{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DiskInjector"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"DiskInjector"},{"type":"text","text":" mounts the guest disk image on the host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"writes a standard macOS LaunchDaemon plist and the user’s script to the data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"volume, then unmounts. When the VM boots, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" picks up the daemon and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"executes the script automatically — no SSH, no agent, no network required."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This uses Apple’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" (ships with macOS) to attach APFS disk images"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and writes only to the data volume (never the Signed System Volume)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Usage","text":"Usage","type":"heading","level":2},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["let scriptURL = URL(fileURLWithPath: \"\/path\/to\/setup.sh\")","let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","try DiskInjector.inject(script: scriptURL, into: bundle)"]},{"anchor":"How-It-Works","text":"How It Works","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"orderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches the guest’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"disk.img"},{"type":"text","text":" using "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":" without mounting"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(to discover the device node)."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Finds and mounts the APFS data volume from the attached disk."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes the user’s script to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/usr\/local\/bin\/spooktacular-user-data.sh"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"on the data volume."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Writes a LaunchDaemon plist to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"\/Library\/LaunchDaemons\/"},{"type":"text","text":" that tells"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"launchd"},{"type":"text","text":" to run the script at boot."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Detaches the disk image so the VM can boot cleanly."}]}]}]},{"anchor":"Thread-Safety","text":"Thread Safety","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All methods are synchronous and use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Process"},{"type":"text","text":" to invoke "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hdiutil"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Call from a background thread if needed to avoid blocking the main thread."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/diskinjector"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"abstract":[{"text":"Injects a user-data script into a VM’s guest disk as a macOS LaunchDaemon.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/DiskInjector","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"DiskInjector","roleHeading":"Enumeration","externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12DiskInjectorO","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"id